* Task 6 fixture (explicit-library-bypass case): APP/CALLER.NSP
* Demonstrates RUN with explicit library-id (second operand).
* RUN 'PGM' 'COMMON' → bypasses the steplib chain and resolves directly
* against the named library (COMMON).
*
* PGM exists in BOTH APP and COMMON:
* - APP/PGM.NSP (current library would normally win)
* - COMMON/PGM.NSP (explicitly named target)
* Expected: resolves to COMMON/PGM.NSP (explicit library beats chain order)
*
* OQ-5: explicit library-id resolves against that library ONLY.
* FR-16: Story 5/6 acceptance criterion — explicit library bypasses chain.

DEFINE DATA
LOCAL
  1 RESULT (A10)
END DEFINE

* RUN with explicit library-id: resolves to COMMON/PGM.NSP, not APP/PGM.NSP
RUN 'PGM' 'COMMON'

MOVE 'OK' TO RESULT

END
